      "content": "This is a pencil and grey wash drawing by Augustijn Claterbos (1750–1828), depicting a harbour scene with two tall stone towers (one partially ruined), boats on a river or harbour basin, and a walled town with a church in the background. The drawing was donated by the Van Weijdom Claterbos family (descendants of the artist) to Teylers Museum in 2003. It is part of a named group of Claterbos works in the collection.",
